subject: Rajasthan History
question_en: What is the first princely state to sign the Pact of Pushkar?
question_hi: पश्चिम या पश्चिमी प्राधीनता की पृथक संशिका को पुष्टिका में संस्थान को क्या है?
explanation_en: The first princely state to sign the Pact of Pushkar was Mewar. The Pact of Pushkar was signed between Maharaja Rao Jodhpur of Mewar (Rajasthan) and Pope Urban II in 1063.
